POLOKWANE – Gr 11 learners at Mitchell House showed off their entrepreneurial skills at the school’s tuckshop takeover last week. Learners marketed their ideas to business studies teacher Charmaine Mathibela which included a pre-order system, choice of products, marketing strategies and lessons learnt in running a tuckshop for the day. The Polokwane Review asked learners what they think makes a great entrepreneur: Read more about the takeover in this week’s Polokwane Review. 